1230: Codex round 3 issues #1, #2, #3: `import 'whatwg-fetch'` does NOT override `global.fetch = jest.fn()` from `jest.setup.js` (the mock is already in place when import runs). Must explicitly reassign `globalThis.fetch`. Also `jest.setup.js` defines `localStorage` as plain `jest.fn()` (non-stateful) — auth tests will fail. Move ALL setup into `enable-msw.ts`; do NOT modify `jest.setup.js`.
1231: 
1232: **Plan rationale (do NOT include in `enable-msw.ts`):** The existing `jest.setup.js` declares `global.fetch = jest.fn()` before any test file loads. A bare `import 'whatwg-fetch'` won't install a real fetch on top of the existing jest mock — the polyfill's IIFE checks `typeof self.fetch !== 'function'` and bails out when the mock is already there. So `installRealFetch()` must (a) remove the existing fetch, (b) bust the require-cache for `whatwg-fetch`, (c) re-require it, (d) verify a real (non-mock) fetch is installed.
